ning ‘bee’ in Hebrew), borne by the nurse of Rebecca (Genesis 35:8) and by a woman judge and prophet (Judges 4–5) who led the Israelites to victory over the Canaanites. It has always been popular as a Jewish name. It was in use among Christians by the mid 16th century and was taken up by the Puritans in the 17th century, in part because the bee was a symbol of industriousness. Since then it has enjoyed enormous popularity, peaking in the 1960s. Among other famous bearers is the actress  Deborah Kerr  (  1921–2007 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomasine de Liston was born about 1470 as the daughter of Robert de Liston and Isabel de Essex. She had at least 1 daughter with John Goldingham Esq. She died about 1520, at the age of 52."},"et":{"about 1470–about 1520":"umbes 1470–umbes 1520","1470–1520":"1470–1520","–Male":"Surnud","–1518":"–1518","1509–1571":"1509–1571","–1484":"–1484","1450–1470":"1450–1470","about 1518":"umbes 1518","about 1470":"umbes 1470","1520":"1520","1484":"1484","1450":"1450","1571":"1571","1509":"1509","about 1520":"umbes 1520","1470":"1470","about 1484":"umbes 1484","1518":"1518","Rougham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rougham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1470–about 1520":"noin 1470–noin 1520","1470–1520":"1470–1520","–Male":"Kuollut","–1518":"–1518","1509–1571":"1509–1571","–1484":"–1484","1450–1470":"1450–1470","about 1518":"noin 1518","about 1470":"noin 1470","1520":"1520","1484":"1484","1450":"1450","1571":"1571","1509":"1509","about 1520":"noin 1520","1470":"1470","about 1484":"noin 1484","1518":"1518","Rougham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Rougham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1470–about 1520":"environ 1470–environ 1520","1470–1520":"1470–1520","–Male":"Décédé","–1518":"–1518","1509–1571":"1509–1571","–1484":"–1484","1450–1470":"1450–1470","about 1518":"environ 1518","about 1470":"environ 1470","1520":"1520","1484":"1484","1450":"1450","1571":"1571","1509":"1509","about 1520":"enviro